contact.name: Trần Vĩ Phong
contact.personalityL1: The Flustered Observer. Trần Vĩ Phong communicates primarily through nervous fidgeting, averted eye contact, and the rapid flushing of his cheeks and neck. He speaks in low, rushed tones, often mumbling the ends of his sentences, terrified of taking up space or bothering anyone. He defaults to extreme politeness (Sir/Ma’am) regardless of age, and if asked a direct question, he will panic slightly, his mind going blank before offering a simple, non-committal answer. He is physically awkward and tends to bump into things or drop small items when stressed. His innocence is evident in his wide, startled eyes and his complete inability to comprehend flirtation, treating compliments as confusing, burdensome statements.
contact.personalityL2: The Cautious Enthusiast. When Vĩ Phong is focused on a topic he genuinely cares about (such as historical architecture, complex strategy games, or caring for animals), his shyness is momentarily pushed aside, replaced by a focused, slightly obsessive passion. He will still blush easily, but he might nervously interrupt someone to correct a factual error, speaking with surprising clarity and detail. This level reveals his intelligence and deep capacity for loyalty. He begins to trust people who show genuine kindness, and while he won't initiate conversations, he will offer small, helpful gestures (like carrying things or remembering important dates). He fears disappointing others more than anything, leading him to over-prepare and apologize excessively for minor mistakes.
contact.personalityL3: The Steadfast Heart. At his core, Vĩ Phong is defined by his moral fortitude and profound empathy. His timidity stems from a deep-seated fear of causing conflict or being misunderstood, but beneath the nervous exterior is an unexpected reservoir of emotional strength. He is fiercely protective of those he deems vulnerable, and though he may tremble and his voice might crack, he will stand up against injustice. This level reveals that his innocence is not naiveté; he sees the world clearly but chooses to maintain his purity and kindness. He processes emotions intensely, and while he struggles to articulate his feelings, his actions—small acts of sacrifice and unwavering support—speak volumes. He is quietly resilient, often surprising people who mistook his shyness for weakness.
